Project Title: BellyUp
Chad Parker, John Vasta, Jinwu Ahn, Zach Benedicto

User Stories:

Customer:
- As a customer, I want to be able to swipe through restaurants so that I can select happy hour deals I am interested in.
- As a customer, I want to view happy hour deals from the swiping interface so that I can view deals concisely
- As a customer, I want to see what the bar atmosphere/food looks like when I am swiping through so I can decide
if I want to visit the restaurant.
- As a customer, I want to be able to set my preferences so that I can match with a restaurant that I would like to 
go to.
- As a customer, I want to save or favorite restaurants so that I can easily revisit and compare my preferred happy hour 
options in the future.
- As a customer, I want to filter and sort available deals by criteria such as price, distance, type of offer,
and time of day so that I can quickly find happy hour deals that match my preferences.

Administrator:
- As an administrator, I want to be able to smoothly input the restaurants with appropriate filters so that I can enter multiple 
restaurants quickly and easily.
- As an administrator, I want to review and moderate user-submitted restaurant entries and customer reviews so that I can ensure all 
listings and feedback meet quality standards before they are published.

Restaurant/Owner:
- As a restaurant owner, I want the app to show accurate information so that the customer does not get misled and angry.
- As a restaurant owner, I want the best pictures of our establishment on the app so that people are more inclined to match with us.
- As a restaurant owner, I want to be able to go on the app myself and see what my competition is offering.

Use Cases:

Chad: Restaurant Filters/ User Preferences, Restaurant Inputting
Zach: Swipe Interface
John: Parking
Jinwu: Restaurant Favorites List

Non-functional Requirements:
Users should be able to swipe through the interface smoothly and as fast as they desire.
Every restaurant's happy hour operation time should follow the same 12-hour, am/pm format.
The app should be able to be used on both iOS and Android.
The app's availability should be 24/7.
The app should resemble "Tinder" but with a unique logo.
The app should show at least 20 different restaurants from the nearby Albany area.
The app should be easy to sign up for and use.
